About Us





Who We Are



Easy E-Learning is a boutique consulting firm with decades of software development experience. We grew up in the era of structured design methodologies, adapted our learnings to the rapid development approaches, and graduated to Agile. Having partnered with many of the original Agile founders, we worked hand-in-hand with them to implement Agile software development practices at companies like IBM, Lotus and Verizon. Raj Heda, President and CEO of Easy E-Learning, is a leading author, teacher and world-renowned industry consultant. Our in-house experts are master’s degree students at Boston University’s Metropolitan College, with decades of industry experience.



  • Devin Dumais, Andras Palfi, and Shailesh Tamrakar are Easy E-Learning's three lead development consultants.
  • Keith Gutfreund leads Easy E-Learning Product Owner and Content Writer teams. Keith studied Electrical and Computer Engineering and has been a hardware and software developer for over 4 decades.
  • Po-Han (John) Huang and Daniela lead Easy E-Learning's Quality certification team. • Mingyang Zu is lead consultant for Easy E-Learning’s Business Analyst certification team.
























What We Do



Easy E-Learning can help you succeed in three ways:



  • Training & Certification: our 1-2 day training courses are specifically designed to prepare you for the Agile certification exams from SAFe, Scrum.org, and Scrum Alliance. You can train with confidence due to our Easy E-Learning guarantee: if you do not succeed in passing the certification, you may re-enroll in the training at no additional cost.
  • Coaching: Easy E-Learning offers customized coaching from our expert staff. We can coach your team, your executives, and your organization. Please contact us for more details.
  • Assessment: Easy E-Learning uniquely offers a suite of detailed assessments to determine your specific organization’s capabilities and needs. See our different assessment offerings here (click link to Assessment page) for more details.
